Personally, out of all these ideas I'm really liking the roguish ones most. Always thought that mercs deserved more roguish abilities - I know dual wield is itself supposed to be roguish, but zerks and blademasters share the ability and are... somewhat far from rogues. Makes it feel like a &quot;light tank&quot; ability instead of a &quot;rogue&quot; ability.<br>
So..... 15 seconds of ~40spec equivalent stealth + safefall/climbwalls, on 15min timer, for 14 pts? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Obviously, like normal stealth, it breaks when you attack and can be seen through etc.<br>
Hell, I'd get that personally. It'd add a great feeling to the class and would actually be tactically useful. (stealth at the start of the fight, reappear on top of a healer. Hmm, thinking about it, that might need a 30min timer instead)<br>
<br>
On the &quot;pbae version of thornweed field&quot; idea, I'd say make don't make it interupt for 30secs or anything. Prolonged interupts like that are just unfair to casters and already too common in RvR, imho.  <p>Cheradenine<br>
